Habitat / Ecology. In the Lizard Island area occurring intertidally in sand and fine sand. Other records in Australia from along the Eastern coasts in Queensland, New South Wales and Victoria (
Blake & Kudenov 1978
); also found in estuaries of New South Wales , in sandy mud at depths of 4–10 m in salinities of 29.8–35 ‰ (
Hutchings & Murray 1984
). Outside Australia the species has been reported from the Golfo de Nicoya ( Costa Rica ) from subtidal depths ( 20 m ) and muddy sand (
Dean 2004
), and at Baja California Sur ( Mexico ) it was collected from 74 m water depth (de León-González 1998 ).
